President Obama met with Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos to discuss Colombia's peace agreement with the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC). President Obama congratulated President Santos and the Colombian people on this historic achievement and acknowledged the challenges ahead in fully implementing the agreement. The two presidents also discussed their commitment to combating organized crime and narcotics trafficking, as well as defending democracy and human rights in the Western Hemisphere. President Obama reiterated the United States' support for Colombia through the Peace Colombia framework announced in February.